cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CE, cs.CV 

The paper deals with the problem of clickstream classification in the fashion industry using machine learning techniques. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as the authors are trying to predict user behavior based on clickstream data. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as the authors preprocess the textual data in the clickstream. Additionally, the authors use computer vision techniques (cs.CV) to extract features from the images in the clickstream. Finally, the paper involves computational engineering (cs.CE) as the authors propose a new neural model for clickstream classification.
